100 MiDispatchFault (
101  IN ULONG_PTR FaultStatus,
102  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
103  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,

111 /*++
112 
113 Routine Description:
114 
115  This routine dispatches a page fault to the appropriate
116  routine to complete the fault.
117 
118 Arguments:
119 
120  FaultStatus - Supplies fault status information bits.
121 
122  VirtualAddress - Supplies the faulting address.
123 
124  PointerPte - Supplies the PTE for the faulting address.
125 
126  PointerProtoPte - Supplies a pointer to the prototype PTE to fault in,
127  NULL if no prototype PTE exists.
128 
129  RecheckAccess - Supplies TRUE if the prototype PTE needs to be checked for
130  access permissions - this is only an issue for forked
131  prototype PTEs that are no-access.
132 
133  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process object. If this
134  parameter is NULL, then the fault is for system
135  space and the process's working set lock is not held.
136  If this parameter is HYDRA_PROCESS, then the fault is for session
137  space and the process's working set lock is not held - rather
138  the session space's working set lock is held.
139 
140  Vad - Supplies the VAD used for sections. May optionally be NULL even
141  for section-based faults, so use purely as an opportunistic hint.
142 
143  TrapInformation - Supplies the trap information.
144 
145 Return Value:
146 
147  NTSTATUS.
148 
149 Environment:
150 
151  Kernel mode, working set mutex held.
152 
153 --*/

162 #define VARIOUS_FLAGS_PFN_HELD 0x02
163 #define VARIOUS_FLAGS_ACCESS_CHECK_NEEDED 0x04
164 #define VARIOUS_FLAGS_LOG_HARD_FAULT 0x08

212 #if DBG
213  EntryIrql = KeGetCurrentIrql ();
214  ASSERT (EntryIrql <= APC_LEVEL);
215  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
216  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (OriginalPte.u.Long = (ULONG_PTR)-1);

219  VariousFlags = 0;
220  LockedProtoPfn = NULL;
221  SessionWs = NULL;
222  StoreInstruction = MI_FAULT_STATUS_INDICATES_WRITE (FaultStatus);
223  WsThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
224 
225  //
226  // Initializing ReadBlock & ReadPte is not needed for correctness, but
227  // without it the compiler cannot compile this code W4 to check for use of
228  // uninitialized variables.
229  //
230 
231  OldIrql = MM_NOIRQL;
232  ReadPte = NULL;
233  ReadBlock = NULL;
234  ProtoProtect.u1.Long = 0;
235 
236  if (PointerProtoPte != NULL) {
237 
238  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(PointerProtoPte));
239 
240  CheckPte = MiGetPteAddress (PointerProtoPte);
241 
242  if (VirtualAddress < MmSystemRangeStart) {
243 
244  NumberOfProtos = 1;
245  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (UsedPageTableHandle = NULL);
246  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (Pfn2 = NULL);
247  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (Protection = 0);
248  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (RealPteContents.u.Long = 0);
249 
250  if ((PointerPte->u.Soft.PageFileHigh != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED) &&
251  (PointerPte->u.Proto.ReadOnly == 0)) {
252 
253  //
254  // Kernel mode access must be verified, go the long way below.
255  //
256 
257  VariousFlags |= VARIOUS_FLAGS_ACCESS_CHECK_NEEDED;
258  }
259  else {
260 
261  //
262  // Opportunistically cluster the transition faults as needed.
263  // When the Vad is non-NULL, the proper access checks have
264  // already been applied across the range (as long as the
265  // PTEs are zero).
266  //
267 
268  if ((Vad != NULL) &&
269  (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType != VadImageMap) &&
270  (Vad->u2.VadFlags2.ExtendableFile == 0) &&
271  (MmAvailablePages > MM_ENORMOUS_LIMIT) &&
272  ((Process->Vm.Flags.MaximumWorkingSetHard == 0) ||
273  (Process->Vm.WorkingSetSize + MmMaxTransitionCluster <= Process->Vm.MaximumWorkingSetSize)) &&
274  (RecheckAccess == FALSE)) {
275 
276  NumberOfProtos = MmMaxTransitionCluster;
277 
278  //
279  // Ensure the cluster doesn't cross the VAD contiguous PTE
280  // limits.
281  //
282 
283  MaxProtos = Vad->LastContiguousPte - PointerProtoPte + 1;
284 
285  if (NumberOfProtos > MaxProtos) {
286  NumberOfProtos = MaxProtos;
287  }
288 
289  //
290  // Ensure the cluster doesn't cross the page containing
291  // the real page table page as we only locked down the
292  // single page.
293  //
294 
295  MaxProtos = (PAGE_SIZE - BYTE_OFFSET (PointerPte)) / sizeof (MMPTE);
296  if (NumberOfProtos > MaxProtos) {
297  NumberOfProtos = MaxProtos;
298  }
299 
300  //
301  // Ensure the cluster doesn't cross the page containing
302  // the prototype PTEs as we only locked down the single
303  // page.
304  //
305 
306  MaxProtos = (PAGE_SIZE - BYTE_OFFSET (PointerProtoPte)) / sizeof (MMPTE);
307  if (NumberOfProtos > MaxProtos) {
308  NumberOfProtos = MaxProtos;
309  }
310 
311  //
312  // Ensure the cluster doesn't cross the VAD limits.
313  //
314 
315  MaxProtos = Vad->EndingVpn - MI_VA_TO_VPN (VirtualAddress) + 1;
316 
317  if (NumberOfProtos > MaxProtos) {
318  NumberOfProtos = MaxProtos;
319  }
320 
321  //
322  // Ensure enough WSLEs are available so we cannot fail to
323  // insert the cluster later.
324  //
325 
326  MaxProtos = 1;
327  WorkingSetIndex = MmWorkingSetList->FirstFree;
328 
329  if ((NumberOfProtos > 1) &&
330  (WorkingSetIndex != WSLE_NULL_INDEX)) {
331 
332  do {
333  if (MmWsle[WorkingSetIndex].u1.Long == (WSLE_NULL_INDEX << MM_FREE_WSLE_SHIFT)) {
334  break;
335  }
336  MaxProtos += 1;
337  WorkingSetIndex = (WSLE_NUMBER) (MmWsle[WorkingSetIndex].u1.Long >> MM_FREE_WSLE_SHIFT);
338  } while (MaxProtos < NumberOfProtos);
339  }
340 
341  if (NumberOfProtos > MaxProtos) {
342  NumberOfProtos = MaxProtos;
343  }
344 
345  //
346  // We have computed the maximum cluster size. Fill the PTEs
347  // and increment the use counts on the page table page for
348  // each PTE we fill (regardless of whether the prototype
349  // cluster pages are already in transition).
350  //
351 
352  ASSERT (VirtualAddress <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS);
353 
354  for (i = 1; i < NumberOfProtos; i += 1) {
355  if ((PointerPte + i)->u.Long != MM_ZERO_PTE) {
356  break;
357  }
358  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte + i, *PointerPte);
359  }
360 
361  NumberOfProtos = i;
362 
363  if (NumberOfProtos > 1) {
364  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (VirtualAddress);
365  MI_INCREMENT_USED_PTES_BY_HANDLE_CLUSTER (UsedPageTableHandle, NumberOfProtos - 1);
366 
367  //
368  // The protection code for the real PTE comes from
369  // the real PTE as it was placed there earlier during
370  // the handling of this fault.
371  //
372 
373  ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection = MI_GET_PROTECTION_FROM_SOFT_PTE (PointerPte);
374  //
375  // Build up a valid PTE so that when the PFN lock is
376  // held, the only additional update to it is for the
377  // actual PFN.
378  //
379 
380  MI_MAKE_VALID_USER_PTE (RealPteContents,
381  0,
382  ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection,
383  PointerPte);
384 
385  if ((StoreInstruction != 0) &&
386  ((ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection & MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) != MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK)) {
387  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (RealPteContents);
388  VariousFlags |= VARIOUS_FLAGS_DIRTY_PTE;
389  }
390 
391  ContainingPageTablePointer = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
392  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (ContainingPageTablePointer->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
393  }
394  }
395  }
396 
397  ProtosProcessed = 0;
398 
399  //
400  // Acquire the PFN lock to synchronize access to prototype PTEs.
401  // This is required as the working set mutex does not prevent
402  // multiple processes from operating on the same prototype PTE.
403  //
404 
405  VariousFlags |= VARIOUS_FLAGS_PFN_HELD;
406  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
407 
408  if (CheckPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
409 
410  //
411  // The working set pushlock must be released here because this
412  // process' working set may be large, but the number of
413  // available pages may be low. In this case, this thread
414  // could end up needing a page to read the prototype PTE
415  // into and would thus wait in MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait,
416  // but since this would be as part of handling the a "new"
417  // fault, it would not release the process working set.
418  //
419  // Increment the number of mapped views so the control area
420  // (and the prototype PTEs) cannot be immediately deleted since
421  // the working set pushlock is going to be released and
422  // reacquired.
423  //
424 
425  CloneDescriptor = NULL;
426  ControlArea = NULL;
427 
428  if ((Vad == NULL) &&
429  ((PAGE_ALIGN (VirtualAddress) != (PVOID) MM_SHARED_USER_DATA_VA))) {
430  Vad = MiLocateAddress (VirtualAddress);
431  ASSERT (Vad != NULL);
432  }
433 
434  if (Vad != NULL) {
435  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory == 0) {
436  ControlArea = Vad->ControlArea;
437  ASSERT (ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews >= 1);
438  ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews += 1;
439  }
440  else {
441 
442  //
443  // Forked private VADs are prototype PTE-backed but
444  // have no control areas. Reference their clone
445  // descriptor instead.
446  //
447 
448  ASSERT (Process->CloneRoot != NULL);
449  CloneDescriptor = MiLocateCloneAddress (Process,
450  PointerProtoPte);
451 
452  ASSERT (CloneDescriptor != NULL);
453  ASSERT (CloneDescriptor->NumberOfReferences >= 1);
454  CloneDescriptor->NumberOfReferences += 1;
455  CloneDescriptor->FinalNumberOfReferences += 1;
456  }
457  }
458 
459  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
460  UNLOCK_WS (WsThread, Process);
461 
462  MmAccessFault (FALSE, PointerProtoPte, KernelMode, NULL);
463 
464  //
465  // Note that the VAD may no longer exist at this point !
466  //
467 
468  if (ControlArea != NULL) {
469 
470  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
471 
472  ASSERT (ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews >= 1);
473  ControlArea->NumberOfMappedViews -= 1;
474 
475  //
476  // See if the control area should be deleted - this
477  // returns with the PFN lock released.
478  //
479 
480  MiCheckControlArea (ControlArea, OldIrql);
481  }
482  else if (CloneDescriptor != NULL) {
483 
484  LOCK_WS (WsThread, Process);
485  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
486 
487  MiDecrementCloneBlockReference (CloneDescriptor,
488  NULL,
489  Process,
490  NULL,
491  OldIrql);
492  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
493 
494  ASSERT (EntryIrql == KeGetCurrentIrql ());
495  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
496 
497  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
498  }
499 
500  LOCK_WS (WsThread, Process);
501 
502  ASSERT (EntryIrql == KeGetCurrentIrql ());
503  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
504 
505  //
506  // Reissue the faulting instruction since while the working set
507  // pushlock was released, the address space may have changed.
508  //
509 
510  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
511  }
512 
513  TempPte = *PointerProtoPte;
514 
515  if (RecheckAccess == TRUE) {
516 
517  //
518  // This is a forked process so shared prototype PTEs
519  // may actually be fork clone prototypes. These have
520  // the protection within the fork clone yet the
521  // hardware PTEs always share it. This must be
522  // checked here for the case where the NO_ACCESS
523  // permission has been put into the fork clone because
524  // it would not necessarily be in the hardware PTEs like
525  // it is for normal prototypes.
526  //
527  // First make sure the proto is in transition or paged
528  // out as only these states can be no access.
529  //
530 
531  if ((TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 0) &&
532  (TempPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0)) {
533 
534  ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection = MI_GET_PROTECTION_FROM_SOFT_PTE (&TempPte);
535  if (ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection == MM_NOACCESS) {
536  ASSERT (MiLocateCloneAddress (Process, PointerProtoPte) != NULL);
537  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
538  return STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
539  }
540  }
541  }
542 
543  //
544  // If the fault can be handled inline (prototype transition or
545  // valid for example), then process it here (eliminating
546  // locked page charges, etc) to reduce PFN hold times.
547  //
548 
549  if ((VariousFlags & VARIOUS_FLAGS_ACCESS_CHECK_NEEDED) == 0) {
550 
551  while (TRUE) {
552 
553  if (TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
554 
555  //
556  // Prototype PTE is valid.
557  //
558 
559  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&TempPte);
560  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT(PageFrameIndex);
561  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
562 
563  }
564  else if ((TempPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
565  (TempPte.u.Soft.Transition == 1)) {
566 
567  //
568  // This is a fault on a PTE which ultimately
569  // decodes to a prototype PTE referencing a
570  // page already in the cache.
571  //
572  // Optimize this path as every cycle counts.
573  //
574 
575  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (&TempPte);
576  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
577 
578  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation != ActiveAndValid);
579 
580  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.ReadInProgress == 1) ||
581  (Pfn1->u4.InPageError == 1) ||
582  (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT)) {
583 
584  break;
585  }
586 
587  MiUnlinkPageFromList (Pfn1);
588 
589  //
590  // Update the PFN database - the reference count
591  // must be incremented as the share count is
592  // going to go from zero to 1.
593  //
594 
595  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 0);
596 
597  //
598  // The PFN reference count will be 1 already
599  // here if the modified writer has begun a write
600  // of this page. Otherwise it's ordinarily 0.
601  //
602  // Note there is no need to apply locked page
603  // charges for this page as we know that the share
604  // count is zero (and the reference count is
605  // unknown). But since we are incrementing both
606  // the share and reference counts by one, the
607  // page will retain its current locked charge
608  // regardless of whether or not it is currently
609  // set.
610  //
611 
612  InterlockedIncrementPfn ((PSHORT)&Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount);
613 
614  //
615  // Update the transition PTE.
616  //
617 
618  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
619  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
620 
621  MI_MAKE_TRANSITION_PROTOPTE_VALID (TempPte,
622  PointerProtoPte);
623 
624  //
625  // If the modified field is set in the PFN database
626  // and this page is not copy on write, then set
627  // the dirty bit. This can be done as the modified
628  // page will not be written to the paging file
629  // until this PTE is made invalid.
630  //
631 
632  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.Modified) &&
633  (TempPte.u.Hard.Write) &&
634  (TempPte.u.Hard.CopyOnWrite == 0)) {
635 
636  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
637  }
638  else {
639  MI_SET_PTE_CLEAN (TempPte);
640  }
641 
642  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerProtoPte, TempPte);
643 
644  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
645  }
646  else {
647  break;
648  }
649 
650  ProtosProcessed += 1;
651 
652  if (ProtosProcessed == NumberOfProtos) {
653 
654  //
655  // This is the last (or only) PFN so use
656  // MiCompleteProtoPteFault so the PFN lock is released
657  // as quickly as possible.
658  //
659 
660  MiCompleteProtoPteFault (StoreInstruction,
661  VirtualAddress,
662  PointerPte,
663  PointerProtoPte,
664  OldIrql,
665  &LockedProtoPfn);
666 
667  VariousFlags &= ~VARIOUS_FLAGS_PFN_HELD;
668  break;
669  }
670 
671  //
672  // Just finish the PFN work here but not the working
673  // set or prefetcher actions as the PFN lock is held
674  // and we want to minimize PFN hold time.
675  //
676 
677  ASSERT (PointerProtoPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
678 
679  Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte = 1;
680 
681  //
682  // Prototype PTE is now valid, make the PTE valid.
683  //
684  // A PTE just went from not present, not transition to
685  // present. The share count and valid count must be
686  // updated in the page table page which contains this PTE.
687  //
688 
689  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
690 
691  //
692  // Ensure the user's attributes do not conflict with
693  // the PFN attributes.
694  //
695 
696  NewPteContents.u.Long = RealPteContents.u.Long;
697  ASSERT (NewPteContents.u.Long != 0);
698 
699  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached) {
700  NOTHING;
701  }
702  else if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiNonCached) {
703 
704  Protection = (MM_PROTECTION_MASK) ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection;
705  Protection &= ~(MM_NOCACHE | MM_WRITECOMBINE);
706 
707  Protection |= MM_NOCACHE;
708  NewPteContents.u.Long = 0;
709  }
710  else if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiWriteCombined) {
711  Protection = (MM_PROTECTION_MASK) ProtoProtect.u1.e1.Protection;
712  Protection &= ~(MM_NOCACHE | MM_WRITECOMBINE);
713  Protection |= MM_WRITECOMBINE;
714  NewPteContents.u.Long = 0;
715  }
716 
717  if (NewPteContents.u.Long == 0) {
718  MI_MAKE_VALID_USER_PTE (NewPteContents,
719  0,
720  Protection,
721  PointerPte);
722 
723  if ((StoreInstruction != 0) &&
724  ((Protection & MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) != MM_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK)) {
725  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (NewPteContents);
726  }
727  }
728 
729  NewPteContents.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
730 
731 #if DBG
732 
733  //
734  // The protection code for the real PTE comes from
735  // the real PTE as it was placed there above.
736  //
737 
738  ProtoProtect2.u1.Long = 0;
739  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Soft.PageFileHigh == MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED);
740  ProtoProtect2.u1.e1.Protection = MI_GET_PROTECTION_FROM_SOFT_PTE(PointerPte);
741 
742  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (OriginalPte,

1464  }
1465  else if (MI_IS_NOCACHE (Protection)) {
1466  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiNonCached, 0);
1467  }
1468 
1469  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != CacheAttribute) {
1470  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageFrameIndex,
1471  CacheAttribute);
1472  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = CacheAttribute;
1473  }
1474 
1475  //
1476  // Fill the PTE.
1477  //
1478 
1479  MI_MAKE_TRANSITION_PTE_VALID (TempPte, ReadPte);
1480  if (StoreInstruction && TempPte.u.Hard.Write) {
1481  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
1482  }
1483  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (ReadPte, TempPte);
1484 
1485  if (PointerProtoPte != NULL) {
1486 
1487  //
1488  // The prototype PTE has been made valid, now make the
1489  // original PTE valid. The original PTE must still be invalid
1490  // otherwise MiWaitForInPageComplete would have returned
1491  // a collision status.
1492  //
1493 
1494  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
1495 
1496  //
1497  // PTE is not valid, continue with operation.
1498  //
1499 
1500  status = MiCompleteProtoPteFault (StoreInstruction,
1501  VirtualAddress,
1502  PointerPte,
1503  PointerProtoPte,
1504  OldIrql,
1505  &LockedProtoPfn);
1506 
1507  //
1508  // Returns with PFN lock released!
1509  //
1510 
1511  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
1512  }
1513  else {
1514 
1515  ASSERT (LockedProtoPfn == NULL);
1516 
1517  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 0);
1518 
1519  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1520 
1521  WorkingSetIndex = MiAddValidPageToWorkingSet (VirtualAddress,
1522  ReadPte,
1523  Pfn1,
1524  0);
1525 
1526  if (WorkingSetIndex == 0) {
1527 
1528  //
1529  // Trim the page since we couldn't add it to the working
1530  // set list at this time.
1531  //
1532 
1533  MiTrimPte (VirtualAddress,
1534  ReadPte,
1535  Pfn1,
1536  Process,
1537  ZeroPte);
1538 
1539  status = STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1540  }
1541 
1542  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
1543  }
1544 
1545  if (VariousFlags & VARIOUS_FLAGS_LOG_HARD_FAULT) {
1546 
1547  HardFaultEvent.ReadOffset = ReadBlock->ReadOffset;
1548  HardFaultEvent.VirtualAddress = VirtualAddress;
1549  HardFaultEvent.FileObject = ReadBlock->FilePointer;
1550  HardFaultEvent.ThreadId = HandleToUlong (WsThread->Cid.UniqueThread);
1551  HardFaultEvent.ByteCount = ReadBlock->Mdl.ByteCount;
1552 
1553  PerfInfoLogBytes (PERFINFO_LOG_TYPE_HARDFAULT,
1554  &HardFaultEvent,
1555  sizeof(HardFaultEvent));
1556  }
1557 
1558  MiFreeInPageSupportBlock (CapturedEvent);
1559 
1560  if (status == STATUS_SUCCESS) {
1561  status = STATUS_PAGE_FAULT_PAGING_FILE;
1562  }
1563  }
1564 
1565  if ((status == STATUS_REFAULT) || (status == STATUS_PTE_CHANGED)) {
1566  status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1567  }
1568 
1569  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
1570 
1571  if (SessionWs != NULL) {
1572  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (WsThread);
1573  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
1574  LOCK_WORKING_SET (WsThread, SessionWs);
1575  }
1576 
1577  if (LockedProtoPfn != NULL) {
1578 
1579  //
1580  // Unlock page containing prototype PTEs.
1581  //
1582 
1583  ASSERT (PointerProtoPte != NULL);
1584  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1585 
1586  //
1587  // The reference count on the prototype PTE page will
1588  // always be greater than 1 if it is a genuine prototype
1589  // PTE pool allocation. However, if it is a fork
1590  // prototype PTE allocation, it is possible the pool has
1591  // already been deallocated and in this case, the LockedProtoPfn
1592  // frame below will be in transition limbo with a share
1593  // count of 0 and a reference count of 1 awaiting our
1594  // final dereference below which will put it on the free list.
1595  //
1596 
1597  ASSERT (LockedProtoPfn->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= 1);
1598  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (LockedProtoPfn);
1599  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1600  }
1601 
1602  ASSERT (EntryIrql == KeGetCurrentIrql ());
1603  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
1604 
1605  return status;
1606 }

1608 
1609 NTSTATUS
1610 MiResolveDemandZeroFault (
1611  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
1612  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
1613  IN PEPROCESS Process,
1614  IN KIRQL OldIrql
1615  )
1616 
1617 /*++
1618 
1619 Routine Description:
1620 
1621  This routine resolves a demand zero page fault.
1622 
1623 Arguments:
1624 
1625  VirtualAddress - Supplies the faulting address.
1626 
1627  PointerPte - Supplies the PTE for the faulting address.
1628 
1629  Process - Supplies a pointer to the process object. If this
1630  parameter is NULL, then the fault is for system
1631  space and the process's working set lock is not held.
1632 
1633  OldIrql - Supplies the IRQL the caller acquired the PFN lock at (MM_NOIRQL
1634  if the caller does not hold the PFN lock). If the caller holds
1635  the PFN lock, the lock cannot be dropped, and the page should
1636  not be added to the working set at this time.
1637 
1638 
1639 Return Value:
1640 
1641  NTSTATUS.
1642 
1643 Environment:
1644 
1645  Kernel mode, PFN lock held conditionally.
1646 
1647 --*/
1648 
1649 
1650 {
1651  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1652  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1653  MMPTE TempPte;
1654  ULONG PageColor;
1655  LOGICAL NeedToZero;
1656  LOGICAL BarrierNeeded;
1657  ULONG BarrierStamp;
1658  WSLE_NUMBER WorkingSetIndex;
1659  LOGICAL ZeroPageNeeded;
1660  LOGICAL CallerHeldPfn;
1661 
1662  NeedToZero = FALSE;
1663  BarrierNeeded = FALSE;
1664  CallerHeldPfn = TRUE;
1665 
1666  //
1667  // Initializing BarrierStamp is not needed for
1668  // correctness but without it the compiler cannot compile this code
1669  // W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
1670  //
1671 
1672  BarrierStamp = 0;
1673 
1674  //
1675  // Initialize variables assuming the operation will succeed.
1676  // If it fails (lack of pages or whatever), it's ok that the
1677  // process' NextPageColor got bumped anyway. The goal is to do
1678  // as much as possible without holding the PFN lock.
1679  //
1680 
1681  if ((Process > HYDRA_PROCESS) && (OldIrql == MM_NOIRQL)) {
1682 
1683  ASSERT (MI_IS_PAGE_TABLE_ADDRESS (PointerPte));
1684 
1685  //
1686  // If a fork operation is in progress and the faulting thread
1687  // is not the thread performing the fork operation, block until
1688  // the fork is completed.
1689  //
1690 
1691  if (Process->ForkInProgress != NULL) {
1692  if (MiWaitForForkToComplete (Process) == TRUE) {
1693  return STATUS_REFAULT;
1694  }
1695  }
1696 
1697  PageColor = MI_PAGE_COLOR_VA_PROCESS (VirtualAddress,
1698  &Process->NextPageColor);
1699 
1700  ASSERT (PageColor != 0xFFFFFFFF);
1701  ZeroPageNeeded = TRUE;
1702  }
1703  else {
1704  if (OldIrql != MM_NOIRQL) {
1705  ZeroPageNeeded = TRUE;
1706  }
1707  else {
1708  ZeroPageNeeded = FALSE;
1709 
1710  //
1711  // For session space, the BSS of an image is typically mapped
1712  // directly as an image, but in the case of images that have
1713  // outstanding user references at the time of section creation,
1714  // the image is copied to a pagefile backed section and then
1715  // mapped in session view space (the destination is mapped in
1716  // system view space). See MiSessionWideReserveImageAddress.
1717  //
1718 
1719  if ((Process == HYDRA_PROCESS) &&
1720  ((MI_IS_SESSION_IMAGE_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress)) ||
1721  ((VirtualAddress >= (PVOID) MiSessionViewStart) &&
1722  (VirtualAddress < (PVOID) MiSessionSpaceWs)))) {
1723 
1724  ZeroPageNeeded = TRUE;
1725  }
1726  }
1727 
1728  PageColor = 0xFFFFFFFF;
1729  }
1730 
1731  if (OldIrql == MM_NOIRQL) {
1732  CallerHeldPfn = FALSE;
1733  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1734  }
1735 
1736  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
1737 
1738  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
1739 
1740  //
1741  // Check to see if a page is available, if a wait is
1742  // returned, do not continue, just return success.
1743  //
1744 
1745  if ((MmAvailablePages >= MM_HIGH_LIMIT) ||
1746  (!MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (Process, OldIrql))) {
1747 
1748  if (PageColor != 0xFFFFFFFF) {
1749 
1750  //
1751  // This page is for a user process and so must be zeroed.
1752  //
1753 
1754  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPageIfAny (PageColor);
1755 
1756  if (PageFrameIndex) {
1757 
1758  //
1759  // This barrier check is needed after zeroing the page
1760  // and before setting the PTE valid. Note since the PFN
1761  // database entry is used to hold the sequence timestamp,
1762  // it must be captured now. Check it at the last possible
1763  // moment.
1764  //
1765 
1766  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1767  BarrierStamp = (ULONG)Pfn1->u4.PteFrame;
1768  }
1769  else {
1770  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (PageColor);
1771  NeedToZero = TRUE;
1772  }
1773  }
1774  else {
1775 
1776  //
1777  // As this is a system page, there is no need to
1778  // remove a page of zeroes, it must be initialized by
1779  // the system before being used.
1780  //
1781 
1782  PageColor = MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_VA (VirtualAddress);
1783 
1784  if (ZeroPageNeeded) {
1785  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPage (PageColor);
1786  }
1787  else {
1788  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveAnyPage (PageColor);
1789  }
1790  }
1791 
1792  MiInitializePfn (PageFrameIndex, PointerPte, 1);
1793 
1794  if (CallerHeldPfn == FALSE) {
1795  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1796  if (Process > HYDRA_PROCESS) {
1797  Process->NumberOfPrivatePages += 1;
1798  BarrierNeeded = TRUE;
1799  }
1800  }
1801 
1802  InterlockedIncrement (&KeGetCurrentPrcb ()->MmDemandZeroCount);
1803 
1804  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1805 
1806  if (NeedToZero) {
1807 
1808  PMMPTE ZeroPte;
1809  PVOID ZeroAddress;
1810 
1811  ASSERT (CallerHeldPfn == FALSE);
1812 
1813  ZeroPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
1814 
1815  if (ZeroPte != NULL) {
1816 
1817  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
1818  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
1819 
1820  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiWriteCombined) {
1821  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
1822  }
1823  else if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiNonCached) {
1824  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
1825  }
1826 
1827  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (ZeroPte, TempPte);
1828 
1829  ZeroAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (ZeroPte);
1830 
1831  KeZeroSinglePage (ZeroAddress);
1832 
1833  MiReleaseSystemPtes (ZeroPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
1834  }
1835  else {
1836  MiZeroPhysicalPage (PageFrameIndex);
1837  }
1838 
1839  //
1840  // Note the stamping must occur after the page is zeroed.
1841  //
1842 
1843  MI_BARRIER_STAMP_ZEROED_PAGE (&BarrierStamp);
1844  }
1845 
1846  //
1847  // As this page is demand zero, set the modified bit in the
1848  // PFN database element and set the dirty bit in the PTE.
1849  //
1850 
1851  MI_SNAP_DATA (Pfn1, PointerPte, 5);
1852 
1853  if (PointerPte <= MiHighestUserPte) {
1854  MI_MAKE_VALID_USER_PTE (TempPte,
1855  PageFrameIndex,
1856  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection,
1857  PointerPte);
1858  }
1859  else {
1860 
1861  //
1862  // Might be system or session or user page directories,
1863  // so go the long way to find out.
1864  //
1865 
1866  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte,
1867  PageFrameIndex,
1868  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection,
1869  PointerPte);
1870  }
1871 
1872  if (TempPte.u.Hard.Write != 0) {
1873  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
1874  }
1875 
1876  if (BarrierNeeded) {
1877  MI_BARRIER_SYNCHRONIZE (BarrierStamp);
1878  }
1879 
1880  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
1881 
1882  if (CallerHeldPfn == FALSE) {
1883 
1884  ASSERT (Pfn1->u1.Event == 0);
1885 
1886  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 0);
1887 
1888  WorkingSetIndex = MiAddValidPageToWorkingSet (VirtualAddress,
1889  PointerPte,
1890  Pfn1,
1891  0);
1892  if (WorkingSetIndex == 0) {
1893 
1894  //
1895  // Trim the page since we couldn't add it to the working
1896  // set list at this time.
1897  //
1898 
1899  MiTrimPte (VirtualAddress,
1900  PointerPte,
1901  Pfn1,
1902  Process,
1903  ZeroPte);
1904 
1905  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
1906  }
1907  }
1908  return STATUS_PAGE_FAULT_DEMAND_ZERO;
1909  }
1910 
1911  if (CallerHeldPfn == FALSE) {
1912  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1913  }
1914  return STATUS_REFAULT;
1915 }
1916 
1917 
1918 NTSTATUS
1919 MiResolveTransitionFault (
1920  IN PVOID FaultingAddress,
1921  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
1922  IN PEPROCESS CurrentProcess,
1923  IN KIRQL OldIrql,
1924  OUT PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT *InPageBlock
1925  )
1926 
1927 /*++
1928 
1929 Routine Description:
1930 
1931  This routine resolves a transition page fault.
1932 
1933 Arguments:
1934 
1935  FaultingAddress - Supplies the faulting address.
1936 
1937  PointerPte - Supplies the PTE for the faulting address.
1938 
1939  CurrentProcess - Supplies a pointer to the process object. If this
1940  parameter is NULL, then the fault is for system
1941  space and the process's working set lock is not held.
1942 
1943  OldIrql - Supplies the IRQL the caller acquired the PFN lock at.
1944 
1945  InPageBlock - Supplies a pointer to an inpage block pointer. The caller
1946  must initialize this to NULL on entry. This routine
1947  sets this to a non-NULL value to signify an inpage block
1948  the caller must free when the caller releases the PFN lock.
1949 
1950 Return Value:
1951 
1952  status, either STATUS_SUCCESS, STATUS_REFAULT or an I/O status
1953  code.
1954 
1955 Environment:
1956 
1957  Kernel mode, PFN lock may optionally be held.
1958 
1959 --*/
1960 
1961 {
1962  MM_PROTECTION_MASK Protection;
1963  MMPFNENTRY PfnFlags;
1964  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1965  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1966  PMMPFN Pfn2;
1967  MMPTE TempPte;
1968  MMPTE TempPte2;
1969  NTSTATUS status;
1970  NTSTATUS PfnStatus;
1971  PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT CapturedEvent;
1972  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
1973  PMMPTE PointerToPteForProtoPage;
1974  WSLE_NUMBER WorkingSetIndex;
1975  ULONG PfnLockHeld;
1976  LOGICAL EnteredCritical;
1977 
1978  //
1979  // ***********************************************************
1980  // Transition PTE.
1981  // ***********************************************************
1982  //
1983 
1984  //
1985  // A transition PTE is either on the free or modified list,
1986  // on neither list because of its ReferenceCount
1987  // or currently being read in from the disk (read in progress).
1988  // If the page is read in progress, this is a collided page
1989  // and must be handled accordingly.
1990  //
1991 
1992  ASSERT (*InPageBlock == NULL);
1993 
1994  if (OldIrql == MM_NOIRQL) {
1995 
1996  PfnLockHeld = FALSE;
1997 
1998  //
1999  // Read the PTE now without the PFN lock so that the PFN entry
2000  // calculations, etc can be done in advance. If it turns out the PTE
2001  // changed after the lock is acquired (should be rare), then
2002  // recalculate.
2003  //
2004 
2005  TempPte2 = *PointerPte;
2006 
2007  PageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER) TempPte2.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber;
2008  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2009 
2010  ASSERT (OldIrql == MM_NOIRQL);
2011  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2012 
2013  TempPte = *PointerPte;
2014 
2015  if ((TempPte.u.Soft.Valid == 0) &&
2016  (TempPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
2017  (TempPte.u.Soft.Transition == 1)) {
2018 
2019  if (TempPte2.u.Long != TempPte.u.Long) {
2020  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (&TempPte);
2021  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2022  }
2023 
2024  NOTHING;
2025  }
2026  else {
2027  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2028  return STATUS_REFAULT;
2029  }
2030  }
2031  else {
2032 
2033  PfnLockHeld = TRUE;
2034  ASSERT (OldIrql != MM_NOIRQL);
2035  TempPte = *PointerPte;
2036 
2037  ASSERT ((TempPte.u.Soft.Valid == 0) &&
2038  (TempPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
2039  (TempPte.u.Soft.Transition == 1));
2040 
2041  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (&TempPte);
2042  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2043  }
2044 
2045  //
2046  // Still in transition format.
2047  //
2048 
2049  InterlockedIncrement (&KeGetCurrentPrcb ()->MmTransitionCount);
2050 
2051  if (Pfn1->u4.InPageError) {
2052 
2053  //
2054  // There was an in-page read error and there are other
2055  // threads colliding for this page, delay to let the
2056  // other threads complete and return. Snap relevant PFN fields
2057  // before releasing the lock as the page may immediately get
2058  // reused.
2059  //
2060 
2061  PfnFlags = Pfn1->u3.e1;
2062  status = Pfn1->u1.ReadStatus;
2063 
2064  if (!PfnLockHeld) {
2065  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2066  }
2067 
2068  if (PfnFlags.ReadInProgress) {
2069 
2070  //
2071  // This only occurs when the page is being reclaimed by the
2072  // compression reaper. In this case, the page is still on the
2073  // transition list (so the ReadStatus is really a flink) so
2074  // substitute a retry status which will induce a delay so the
2075  // compression reaper can finish taking the page (and PTE).
2076  //
2077 
2078  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
2079  }
2080 
2081  ASSERT (!NT_SUCCESS(status));
2082 
2083  return status;
2084  }
2085 
2086  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.ReadInProgress) {
2087 
2088  //
2089  // Collided page fault.
2090  //
2091 
2092  CapturedEvent = (PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT)Pfn1->u1.Event;
2093 
2094  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
2095 
2096  if (CapturedEvent->Thread == CurrentThread) {
2097 
2098  //
2099  // This detects when the Io APC completion routine accesses
2100  // the same user page (ie: during an overlapped I/O) that
2101  // the user thread has already faulted on.
2102  //
2103  // This can result in a fatal deadlock and so must
2104  // be detected here. Return a unique status code so the
2105  // (legitimate) callers know this has happened so it can be
2106  // handled properly, ie: Io must request a callback from
2107  // the Mm once the first fault has completed.
2108  //
2109  // Note that non-legitimate callers must get back a failure
2110  // status so the thread can be terminated.
2111  //
2112 
2113 #if DBG
2114 
2115 #if defined (_AMD64_)
2116 
2117  {
2118  //
2119  // Do not assert if there are stack walks in progress since
2120  // this can be ok. The stack walking code will deal with
2121  // the in page error raised due to this situation.
2122  //
2123 
2124  extern LONG RtlpStackWalksInProgress;
2125 
2126  if (RtlpStackWalksInProgress == 0) {
2127  ASSERT (CurrentThread->ActiveFaultCount >= 1);
2128  }
2129  }
2130 
2131 #else
2132  ASSERT (CurrentThread->ActiveFaultCount >= 1);
2133 
2134 #endif
2135 
2136 #endif
2137 
2138  CurrentThread->ApcNeeded = 1;
2139 
2140  if (!PfnLockHeld) {
2141  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2142  }
2143  return STATUS_MULTIPLE_FAULT_VIOLATION;
2144  }
2145 
2146  //
2147  // Increment the reference count for the page so it won't be
2148  // reused until all collisions have been completed.
2149  //
2150 
2151  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 0);
2152  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
2153 
2154  InterlockedIncrementPfn ((PSHORT)&Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount);
2155 
2156  //
2157  // Careful synchronization is applied to the WaitCount field so
2158  // that freeing of the inpage block can occur lock-free. Note
2159  // that the ReadInProgress bit on each PFN is set and cleared while
2160  // holding the PFN lock. Inpage blocks are always (and must be)
2161  // freed _AFTER_ the ReadInProgress bit is cleared.
2162  //
2163 
2164  InterlockedIncrement (&CapturedEvent->WaitCount);
2165 
2166  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2167 
2168  CurrentThread->ActiveFaultCount += 1;
2169  EnteredCritical = FALSE;
2170 
2171  if (CurrentProcess == HYDRA_PROCESS) {
2172  UNLOCK_WORKING_SET (CurrentThread,
2173  &MmSessionSpace->GlobalVirtualAddress->Vm);
2174  }
2175  else if (CurrentProcess != NULL) {
2176 
2177  //
2178  // APCs must be explicitly disabled to prevent suspend APCs from
2179  // interrupting this thread before the wait has been issued.
2180  // Otherwise the APC can result in this page being locked
2181  // indefinitely until the suspend is released.
2182  //
2183 
2184  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
2185 
2186  UNLOCK_WS (CurrentThread, CurrentProcess);
2187  EnteredCritical = TRUE;
2188  }
2189  else {
2190  UNLOCK_SYSTEM_WS (CurrentThread);
2191  }
2192 
2193  //
2194  // Set the inpage block address as the waitcount was incremented
2195  // above and therefore the free must be done by our caller.
2196  //
2197 
2198  *InPageBlock = CapturedEvent;
2199 
2200  status = MiWaitForInPageComplete (Pfn1,
2201  PointerPte,
2202  FaultingAddress,
2203  &TempPte,
2204  CapturedEvent,
2205  CurrentProcess);
2206 
2207  //
2208  // MiWaitForInPageComplete RETURNS WITH THE WORKING SET LOCK
2209  // AND PFN LOCK HELD!!!
2210  //
2211 
2212  CurrentThread->ActiveFaultCount -= 1;
2213 
2214  if (EnteredCritical == TRUE) {
2215  KeLeaveCriticalRegionThread (&CurrentThread->Tcb);
2216  }

2226  // If so, try to free the physical page, wait a
2227  // half second and return a status of PTE_CHANGED.
2228  // This will result in success being returned to
2229  // the user and the fault will occur again and should
2230  // not be a transition fault this time.

2261  }

2264  // Instead of returning status, always return STATUS_REFAULT.
2265  // This is to support filesystems that save state in the
2266  // ETHREAD of the thread that serviced the fault ! Since
2267  // collided threads never enter the filesystem, their ETHREADs
2268  // haven't been hacked up. Since this only matters when
2269  // errors occur (specifically STATUS_VERIFY_REQUIRED today),
2270  // retry any failed I/O in the context of each collider
2271  // to give the filesystems ample opportunity.
2272  //

2275  }
2276  }

2280  // PTE refers to a normal transition PTE.
2281  //
2282

2286  // Check available pages so that a machine which is low on memory
2287  // can stop this thread from gobbling up the pages from every modified
2288  // write that completes because that would starve waiting threads.
2289  //
2290  // Another scenario is if the system is utilizing a hardware
2291  // compression cache. Checking ensures that only a safe amount
2292  // of the compressed virtual cache is directly mapped so that
2293  // if the hardware gets into trouble, we can bail it out.
2294  //

2303  // repeat this fault.
2304  //

2308  }
2309

2312  // working set mutex in order to make pages available.
2313  //
2314 
2315  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
2316  }
2317 
2318  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.InPageError == 0);
2319  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid) {
2320

2322  // This page must contain an MmSt allocation of prototype PTEs.
2323  // Because these types of pages reside in paged pool (or special
2324  // pool) and are part of the system working set, they can be
2325  // trimmed at any time regardless of the share count. However,
2326  // if the share count is nonzero, then the page state will
2327  // remain active and the page will remain in memory - but the

2336  (Pfn1->PteAddress <= MiGetPteAddress(MmSpecialPoolEnd))));

2339  // Don't increment the valid PTE count for the
2340  // page table page.
2341  //
2342

2344  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
2345  }

2347

2353  //
2354

2361  //

2370  //

2389  //

2391  // system cache virtual address, the PointerPte points at the pool
2392  // allocation containing the relevant prototype PTEs. This page
2393  // may have been trimmed because it isn't locked down during
2394  // processing of system space virtual address faults.
2395  //

2398

2400

2402

2409  (Pfn2->u4.InPageError));
2410

2412

2414  (Pfn2->PteAddress <= MiGetPteAddress(MmPagedPoolEnd))) ||
2415  ((Pfn2->PteAddress >= MiGetPteAddress(MmSpecialPoolStart)) &&
2416  (Pfn2->PteAddress <= MiGetPteAddress(MmSpecialPoolEnd))));

2421  //

2424  ASSERT (Pfn2->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);

2429  //
2430

2432  Protection &= ~(MM_NOCACHE | MM_WRITECOMBINE);

2435  NOTHING;
2436  }
2437  else if (Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiNonCached) {
2438  Protection |= MM_NOCACHE;
2439  }
2440  else if (Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiWriteCombined) {
2441  Protection |= MM_WRITECOMBINE;
2442  }

2446  Protection,
2447  PointerToPteForProtoPage);
2448

2460  //
2461

2466  }
2467  else {

2469  }
2470

2474 
2475  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 0);
2476

2480  PointerPte,

2482  0);

2488  // set list at this time.
2489  //
2490 
2491  MiTrimPte (FaultingAddress,
2492  PointerPte,
2493  Pfn1,
2494  CurrentProcess,
2495  ZeroPte);
2496 
2497 
2498  return STATUS_NO_MEMORY;
2499  }
2500  }
2501  return STATUS_PAGE_FAULT_TRANSITION;

2516

2518 
2519  This routine builds the MDL and other structures to allow a
2520  read operation on a page file for a page fault.
2521 
2522 Arguments:
2523 
2524  FaultingAddress - Supplies the faulting address.

2595  //

3666  //

3679  //

3689  //

3697  }

3723  //

5125  //
5126 
5127  InterlockedExchangePte (PointerPde, TempPde.u.Long);
5128  return STATUS_WAIT_1;
5129  }
5130 
5131 #if DBG
5132  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
5133  "MiCheckPdeForSessionSpace: No Session PDE for PTE %p, %p\n",
5134  PointerPde->u.Long, SessionVirtualAddress);
5135 
5136  DbgBreakPoint ();
5137 #endif
5138  return STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
5139  }
5140 
5141  if (MI_IS_SESSION_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress) == FALSE) {
5142 
5143  //
5144  // Not a session space fault - tell the caller to try other handlers.
5145  //
5146 
5147  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
5148  }
5149 
5150  //
5151  // Handle PDE faults for references in the session space.
5152  // Verify that the current process has a session space.
5153  //
5154 
5155  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmSessionSpace);
5156 
5157  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5158 
5159 #if DBG
5160  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
5161  "MiCheckPdeForSessionSpace: No current session for VA %p\n",
5162  VirtualAddress);
5163 
5164  DbgBreakPoint ();
5165 #endif
5166  return STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
5167  }
5168 
5169  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (VirtualAddress);
5170 
5171  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5172 
5173  //
5174  // Calculate the session space PDE index and load the
5175  // PDE from the session space table for this session.
5176  //
5177 
5178  Index = MiGetPdeSessionIndex (VirtualAddress);
5179 
5180  PointerPde->u.Long = MmSessionSpace->PageTables[Index].u.Long;
5181 
5182  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
5183  return STATUS_WAIT_1;
5184  }
5185 
5186 #if DBG
5187  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
5188  "MiCheckPdeForSessionSpace: No Session PDE for VA %p, %p\n",
5189  PointerPde->u.Long, VirtualAddress);
5190 
5191  DbgBreakPoint ();
5192 #endif
5193 
5194  return STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
5195  }
5196 
5197  //
5198  // Tell the caller to continue with other fault handlers.
5199  //
5200 
5201  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
5202 }
5203 #endif

5206 VOID
5207 MiInitializePfn (
5208  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
5209  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
5210  IN ULONG ModifiedState
5211  )
5212 
5213 /*++
5214 
5215 Routine Description:
5216 
5217  This function initializes the specified PFN element to the
5218  active and valid state.
5219 
5220 Arguments:
5221 
5222  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the page frame number to initialize.
5223 
5224  PointerPte - Supplies the pointer to the PTE which caused the page fault.
5225 
5226  ModifiedState - Supplies the state to set the modified field in the PFN
5227  element for this page, either 0 or 1.
5228 
5229 Return Value:
5230 
5231  None.
5232 
5233 Environment:
5234 
5235  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, PFN lock held.
5236 
5237 --*/
5238 
5239 {
5240  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5241  PMMPFN Pfn2;
5242  PMMPTE PteFramePointer;
5243  PFN_NUMBER PteFramePage;
5244  MM_PROTECTION_MASK Protection;
5245  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE NewCacheAttribute;
5246 
5247  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
5248 
5249  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5250  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
5251  NewCacheAttribute = MiCached;
5252 
5253  //
5254  // If the PTE is currently valid, an address space is being built,
5255  // just make the original PTE demand zero.
5256  //
5257 
5258  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
5259 
5260  //
5261  // The only time this should happen is for the initial process pages
5262  // created (and initialized) out of context. They must be in order
5263  // to attach and then initialize the process, and
5264  // MmCreateProcessAddressSpace assumes responsibility for detecting
5265  // and preventing TB attribute conflicts for this case, so we don't
5266  // need to here.
5267  //
5268 
5269  ASSERT (PsGetCurrentProcess()->Vm.WorkingSetSize == 0);
5270 
5271  ASSERT (!MI_IS_WRITE_COMBINE_ENABLED (PointerPte));
5272  ASSERT (!MI_IS_CACHING_DISABLED (PointerPte));
5273  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached);
5274 
5275  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
5276 
5277 #if defined (_AMD64_)
5278  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.NoExecute == 0) {
5279  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE;
5280  }
5281 #endif
5282 
5283 #if defined(_X86PAE_)
5284  if (MmPaeMask != 0) {
5285  if ((PointerPte->u.Long & MmPaeMask) == 0) {
5286  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE;
5287  }
5288  }
5289 #endif
5290  }
5291  else {
5292 
5293  Pfn1->OriginalPte = *PointerPte;
5294 
5295  ASSERT (!((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
5296  (Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Transition == 1)));
5297 
5298  Protection = (MM_PROTECTION_MASK) PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection;
5299 
5300  if (MI_IS_WRITECOMBINE (Protection)) {
5301  NewCacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiWriteCombined, 0);
5302  }
5303  else if (MI_IS_NOCACHE (Protection)) {
5304  NewCacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiNonCached, 0);
5305  }
5306 
5307  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != NewCacheAttribute) {
5308  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageFrameIndex,
5309  NewCacheAttribute);
5310  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = NewCacheAttribute;
5311  }
5312  }
5313 
5314  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0);
5315  Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount += 1;
5316 
5317  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
5318  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
5319 
5320  if (ModifiedState == 1) {
5321  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0xB);
5322  }
5323  else {
5324  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 0, 0x26);
5325  }
5326 
5327 #if defined (_WIN64)
5328  Pfn1->UsedPageTableEntries = 0;
5329 #endif
5330 
5331  //
5332  // Determine the page frame number of the page table page which
5333  // contains this PTE.
5334  //
5335 
5336  PteFramePointer = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
5337  if (PteFramePointer->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5338 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5339  if (!NT_SUCCESS(MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (PointerPte))) {
5340 #endif
5341  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
5342  0x61940,
5343  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
5344  (ULONG_PTR)PteFramePointer->u.Long,
5345  (ULONG_PTR)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte));
5346 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5347  }
5348 #endif
5349  }
5350  PteFramePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PteFramePointer);
5351  ASSERT (PteFramePage != 0);
5352  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = PteFramePage;
5353 
5354  //
5355  // Increment the share count for the page table page containing
5356  // this PTE.
5357  //
5358 
5359  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteFramePage);
5360 
5361  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
5362 
5363  return;
5364 }

5366 VOID

5392 
5393  None.
5394

5396 
5397  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, PFN lock held.
5398 
5399 --*/
5400 
5401 {
5402  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5403  PMMPFN Pfn2;
5404  PMMPTE PteFramePointer;
5405  PFN_NUMBER PteFramePage;
5406  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE NewCacheAttribute;
5407 
5408  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
5409 
5410  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
5411

5413  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
5414

5416  // An address space is being built, just make the original PTE demand zero.
5417  //
5418

5420 
5421 #if defined (_AMD64_)

5423  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE;
5424  }
5425 #endif
5426 
5427 #if defined(_X86PAE_)
5428  if (MmPaeMask != 0) {
5429  if ((NewPteContents.u.Long & MmPaeMask) == 0) {
5430  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection = MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE;
5431  }
5432  }
5433 #endif
5434 
5435  NewCacheAttribute = MiCached;
5436 
5437  if (MI_IS_WRITE_COMBINE_ENABLED (&NewPteContents)) {
5438  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection |= MM_WRITECOMBINE;
5439  NewCacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiWriteCombined, 0);
5440  }
5441  else if (MI_IS_CACHING_DISABLED (&NewPteContents)) {

5448  //

5454  }

5457  Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount += 1;
5458 
5459  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
5460  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
5461 
5462  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0xB);
5463 
5464 #if defined (_WIN64)
5465  Pfn1->UsedPageTableEntries = 0;
5466 #endif
5467 
5468  //
5469  // Determine the page frame number of the page table page which
5470  // contains this PTE.
5471  //
5472 
5473  PteFramePointer = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
5474  if (PteFramePointer->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5475 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5476  if (!NT_SUCCESS(MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (PointerPte))) {
5477 #endif
5478  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
5479  0x61940,
5480  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
5481  (ULONG_PTR)PteFramePointer->u.Long,
5482  (ULONG_PTR)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte));
5483 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5484  }
5485 #endif
5486  }
5487  PteFramePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PteFramePointer);
5488  ASSERT (PteFramePage != 0);
5489  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = PteFramePage;
5490 
5491  //
5492  // Increment the share count for the page table page containing
5493  // this PTE.
5494  //
5495 
5496  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteFramePage);
5497 
5498  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;

5500  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, NewPteContents);

5644 Routine Description:
5645 
5646  This function initializes the specified PFN element to the
5647  transition / read-in-progress state for an in-page operation.
5648 
5649 
5650 Arguments:
5651 
5652  Mdl - Supplies a pointer to the MDL.
5653 
5654  BasePte - Supplies the pointer to the PTE which the first page in
5655  the MDL maps.
5656 
5657  Event - Supplies the event which is to be set when the I/O operation
5658  completes.

5661  -1 indicates no WSLE is required because
5662  this is a prototype PTE.

5664 Return Value:

5666  None.
5667

5669 
5670  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, PFN lock held.

5673 
5674 {
5675  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5676  PMMPFN Pfn2;

5678  PFN_NUMBER PteFramePage;

5683  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE NewCacheAttribute;

5685

5687 
5688  PteFramePage = 0;
5689  PteFramePointer = 0;
5690  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (NewCacheAttribute = MiCached);
5691 
5692  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
5693

5695

5697

5699

5701  Pfn1->u1.Event = Event;
5702  Pfn1->PteAddress = BasePte;
5703  Pfn1->OriginalPte = *BasePte;
5704  if (WorkingSetIndex == MI_PROTOTYPE_WSINDEX) {
5705  Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte = 1;
5706  }

5709 
5710  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount = 0;
5711  Pfn1->u3.e1.ReadInProgress = 1;
5712 
5713  Protection = (MM_PROTECTION_MASK) BasePte->u.Soft.Protection;
5714 
5715  NewCacheAttribute = MiCached;
5716 
5717  if (MI_IS_WRITECOMBINE (Protection)) {
5718  NewCacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiWriteCombined, 0);
5719  }
5720  else if (MI_IS_NOCACHE (Protection)) {
5721  NewCacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (MiNonCached, 0);
5722  }

5735  // contains this PTE.
5736  //

5739  PteFramePointer = MiGetPteAddress (BasePte);
5740  }
5741  else {
5742  PteFramePointer += 1;
5743  ASSERT (PteFramePointer == MiGetPteAddress (BasePte));
5744  }
5745 
5746  if (PteFramePointer->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5747 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5748  if (!NT_SUCCESS(MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (BasePte))) {
5749 #endif

5788  Page += 1;

5790  }
5791

5793  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB_FOR_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (NewCacheAttribute);

5799 VOID

5805 /*++

5821 
5822  None.
5823 
5824 Environment:
5825 
5826  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, PFN lock held.
5827 
5828 --*/
5829 
5830 {
5831  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5832  PMMPFN Pfn2;
5833  PMMPTE PteFramePointer;
5834  PFN_NUMBER PteFramePage;
5835  MMPTE TempPte;
5836 
5837  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
5838  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5839  Pfn1->u1.Event = NULL;
5840  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
5841  Pfn1->OriginalPte = *PointerPte;
5842  ASSERT (!((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
5843  (Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Transition == 1)));
5844 
5845  //
5846  // Don't change the reference count (it should already be 1).
5847  //
5848 
5849  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount = 0;
5850 
5851  //
5852  // No WSLE is required because this is a prototype PTE.
5853  //
5854 
5855  Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte = 1;
5856 
5857  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = TransitionPage;
5858 
5859  //
5860  // Determine the page frame number of the page table page which
5861  // contains this PTE.
5862  //
5863 
5864  PteFramePointer = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
5865  if (PteFramePointer->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
5866 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5867  if (!NT_SUCCESS(MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (PointerPte))) {
5868 #endif
5869  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
5870  0x61940,
5871  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
5872  (ULONG_PTR)PteFramePointer->u.Long,
5873  (ULONG_PTR)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte));
5874 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)
5875  }
5876 #endif
5877  }
5878 
5879  PteFramePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PteFramePointer);
5880  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = PteFramePage;
5881

5883  // Put the PTE into the transition state, no cache flush needed as
5884  // PTE is still not valid.
5885  //
5886 
5887  MI_MAKE_TRANSITION_PTE (TempPte,
5888  PageFrameIndex,
5889  PointerPte->u.Soft.Protection,
5890  PointerPte);
5891 
5892  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
5893 
5894  //
5895  // Increment the share count for the page table page containing
5896  // this PTE as the PTE just went into the transition state.
5897  //
5898 
5899  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PteFramePage);
5900  ASSERT (PteFramePage != 0);
5901  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
5902 
5903  return;
5904 }

5906 VOID
5907 MiInitializeCopyOnWritePfn (

6008 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS < 3)

6010 #endif
6011  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
6012  0x61940,
6013  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
6014  (ULONG_PTR)PteFramePointer->u.Long,
6015  (ULONG_PTR)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte));

6036 BOOLEAN
6037 MiIsAddressValid (
6038  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
6039  IN LOGICAL UseForceIfPossible
6040  )
6041 
6042 /*++
6043 
6044 Routine Description:
6045 
6046  For a given virtual address this function returns TRUE if no page fault
6047  will occur for a read operation on the address, FALSE otherwise.
6048 
6049  Note that after this routine was called, if appropriate locks are not
6050  held, a non-faulting address could fault.
6051 
6052 Arguments:
6053 
6054  VirtualAddress - Supplies the virtual address to check.
6055 
6056  UseForceIfPossible - Supplies TRUE if the address should be forced valid
6057  if possible.
6058 
6059 Return Value:
6060 
6061  TRUE if no page fault would be generated reading the virtual address,
6062  FALSE otherwise.
6063 
6064 Environment:
6065 
6066  Kernel mode.
6067 
6068 --*/
6069 
6070 {
6071  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6072  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (UseForceIfPossible);
6073 
6074 #if defined (_AMD64_)
6075 
6076  //
6077  // If this is within the physical addressing range, just return TRUE.
6078  //
6079 
6080  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(VirtualAddress)) {
6081 
6082  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6083 
6084  //
6085  // Only bound with MmHighestPhysicalPage once Mm has initialized.
6086  //
6087 
6088  if (MmHighestPhysicalPage != 0) {
6089 
6090  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN(VirtualAddress);
6091 
6092  if (PageFrameIndex > MmHighestPhysicalPage) {
6093  return FALSE;
6094  }
6095  }
6096 
6097  return TRUE;
6098  }
6099 
6100 #endif
6101 
6102  //
6103  // If the address is not canonical then return FALSE as the caller (which
6104  // may be the kernel debugger) is not expecting to get an unimplemented
6105  // address bit fault.
6106  //
6107 
6108  if (MI_RESERVED_BITS_CANONICAL(VirtualAddress) == FALSE) {
6109  return FALSE;
6110  }
6111 
6112 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
6113  PointerPte = MiGetPxeAddress (VirtualAddress);
6114  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6115  return FALSE;
6116  }
6117 #endif
6118 
6119 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
6120  PointerPte = MiGetPpeAddress (VirtualAddress);
6121 
6122  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6123  return FALSE;
6124  }
6125 #endif
6126 
6127  PointerPte = MiGetPdeAddress (VirtualAddress);
6128  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6129  return FALSE;
6130  }
6131 
6132  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPte)) {
6133  return TRUE;
6134  }
6135 
6136  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
6137  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6138  return FALSE;
6139  }
6140 
6141  //
6142  // Make sure we're not treating a page directory as a page table here for
6143  // the case where the page directory is mapping a large page. This is
6144  // because the large page bit is valid in PDE formats, but reserved in
6145  // PTE formats and will cause a trap. A virtual address like c0200000 (on
6146  // x86) triggers this case.
6147  //
6148 
6149  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPte)) {
6150  return FALSE;
6151  }
6152 
6153  return TRUE;
6154 }

6190 VOID
6191 MiInitializePfnForOtherProcess (
6192  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
6193  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
6194  IN PFN_NUMBER ContainingPageFrame
6195  )
6196 
6197 /*++
6198 
6199 Routine Description:
6200 
6201  This function initializes the specified PFN element to the
6202  active and valid state with the dirty bit on in the PTE and
6203  the PFN database marked as modified.
6204 
6205  As this PTE is not visible from the current process, the containing
6206  page frame must be supplied at the PTE contents field for the
6207  PFN database element are set to demand zero.
6208 
6209 Arguments:
6210 
6211  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the page frame number of which to initialize.
6212 
6213  PointerPte - Supplies the pointer to the PTE which caused the
6214  page fault.
6215 
6216  ContainingPageFrame - Supplies the page frame number of the page
6217  table page which contains this PTE.
6218  If the ContainingPageFrame is 0, then
6219  the ShareCount for the
6220  containing page is not incremented.
6221 
6222 Return Value:
6223 
6224  None.
6225 
6226 Environment:
6227 
6228  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, PFN lock held.
6229 
6230 --*/
6231 
6232 {
6233  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6234  PMMPFN Pfn2;
6235 
6236  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6237  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
6238 
6239  //
6240  // Note that pages allocated this way are for the kernel and thus
6241  // never have split permissions in the PTE or the PFN.
6242  //
6243 
6244  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
6245  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0);
6246  Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount = 1;
6247 
6248  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount += 1;
6249  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
6250 
6251  //
6252  // Set the page attribute to cached even though it isn't really mapped
6253  // into a TB entry yet - it will be when the I/O completes and in the
6254  // future, may get paged in and out multiple times and will be marked
6255  // as cached in those transactions also. If in fact the driver stack
6256  // wants to map it some other way for the transfer, the correct mapping
6257  // will get used regardless.
6258  //
6259 
6260  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
6261  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_CACHED_ATTRIBUTE ();
6262  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
6263  }
6264 
6265  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0xD);
6266 
6267  Pfn1->u4.InPageError = 0;
6268 
6269  //
6270  // Increment the share count for the page table page containing
6271  // this PTE.
6272  //
6273 
6274  if (ContainingPageFrame != 0) {
6275  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = ContainingPageFrame;
6276  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (ContainingPageFrame);
6277  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
6278  }
6279  return;
6280 }

6361 VOID
6362 MiTrimPte (
6363  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
6364  IN PMMPTE PointerPte,
6365  IN PMMPFN Pfn1,
6366  IN PEPROCESS CurrentProcess,
6367  IN MMPTE NewPteContents
6368  )
6369 
6370 /*++
6371 
6372 Routine Description:
6373 
6374  This routine removes the specified virtual address from a page table
6375  page. Note there is no working set list entry for this address.
6376 
6377 Arguments:
6378 
6379  VirtualAddress - Supplies the address to remove.
6380 
6381  PointerPte - Supplies a pointer to the PTE that is now valid.
6382 
6383  Pfn1 - Supplies the PFN database element for the physical page
6384  mapped by the virtual address.
6385 
6386  CurrentProcess - Supplies NULL (ie: system cache), HYDRA_PROCESS (ie:
6387  a session) or anything else (ie: process).
6388 
6389  NewPteContents - Supplies the new PTE contents to place in the PTE. This
6390  is only used for prototype PTEs - private PTEs are
6391  always encoded with the Pfn's OriginalPte information.
6392 
6393 Return Value:
6394 
6395  None.
6396 
6397 Environment:
6398 
6399  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, working set lock. PFN lock NOT held.
6400 
6401 --*/
6402 
6403 {
6404  KIRQL OldIrql;
6405  MMPTE TempPte;
6406  MMPTE PreviousPte;
6407  PMMPTE ContainingPageTablePage;
6408  PMMPFN Pfn2;
6409  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6410  PFN_NUMBER PageTableFrameIndex;
6411  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
6412 
6413  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
6414 
6415  PageFrameIndex = MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (Pfn1);
6416 
6417  // Working set mutex must be held.
6418  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= APC_LEVEL);
6419  ASSERT (KeAreAllApcsDisabled () == TRUE);
6420 
6421  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte) {
6422 
6423  ASSERT (MI_IS_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1) == 0);
6424 
6425  //
6426  // This is a prototype PTE. The PFN database does not contain
6427  // the contents of this PTE it contains the contents of the
6428  // prototype PTE. This PTE must be reconstructed to contain
6429  // a pointer to the prototype PTE.
6430  //
6431  // The working set list entry contains information about
6432  // how to reconstruct the PTE.
6433  //
6434 
6435  TempPte = NewPteContents;
6436  ASSERT (NewPteContents.u.Proto.Prototype == 1);
6437 
6438  //
6439  // Decrement the share count of the containing page table
6440  // page as the PTE for the removed page is no longer valid
6441  // or in transition.
6442  //
6443 
6444  ContainingPageTablePage = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
6445 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
6446  ASSERT (ContainingPageTablePage->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6447 #else
6448  if (ContainingPageTablePage->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6449  if (!NT_SUCCESS(MiCheckPdeForPagedPool (PointerPte))) {
6450  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
6451  0x61940,
6452  (ULONG_PTR) PointerPte,
6453  (ULONG_PTR) ContainingPageTablePage->u.Long,
6454  (ULONG_PTR) VirtualAddress);
6455  }
6456  }
6457 #endif
6458  PageTableFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (ContainingPageTablePage);
6459  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTableFrameIndex);
6460 
6461  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6462  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, PageTableFrameIndex);
6463  }
6464  else {
6465 
6466  //
6467  // This is a private page, make it transition.
6468  //
6469  // Assert that the share count is 1 for all user mode pages.
6470  //
6471 
6472  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1) ||
6473  (VirtualAddress > (PVOID)MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS));
6474 
6475  if (MI_IS_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1)) {
6476  TempPte.u.Long = 0;
6477  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
6478  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6479  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn2, Pfn1->u4.PteFrame);
6480  }
6481  else {
6482  TempPte = *PointerPte;
6483 
6484  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (TempPte,
6485  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Protection);
6486  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6487  }
6488  }
6489 
6490  PreviousPte = *PointerPte;
6491 
6492  ASSERT (PreviousPte.u.Hard.Valid == 1);
6493 
6494  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
6495 
6496  MI_CAPTURE_DIRTY_BIT_TO_PFN (&PreviousPte, Pfn1);
6497 
6498  if ((CurrentProcess == NULL) || (CurrentProcess == HYDRA_PROCESS)) {
6499  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VirtualAddress, TRUE);
6500  }
6501  else {
6502 
6503  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VirtualAddress, FALSE);
6504 
6505  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 0) &&
6506  (MI_IS_PTE_DIRTY(PreviousPte)) &&
6507  (CurrentProcess->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_USING_WRITE_WATCH)) {
6508 
6509  //
6510  // This process has (or had) write watch VADs.
6511  // Search now for a write watch region encapsulating
6512  // the PTE being invalidated.
6513  //
6514 
6515  MiCaptureWriteWatchDirtyBit (CurrentProcess, VirtualAddress);
6516  }
6517  }
6518 
6519  MiDecrementShareCountInline (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
6520 
6521  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);

6524 PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT
6525 MiGetInPageSupportBlock (
6526  IN KIRQL OldIrql,
6527  OUT PNTSTATUS Status
6528  )
6529 
6530 /*++
6531 
6532 Routine Description:
6533 
6534  This routine acquires an inpage support block. If none are available,
6535  the PFN lock will be released and reacquired to add an entry to the list.
6536  NULL will then be returned.
6537 
6538 Arguments:
6539 
6540  OldIrql - Supplies the IRQL the caller acquired the PFN lock at (or
6541  MM_NOIRQL if the caller did not acquire the PFN at all).
6542 
6543  Status - Supplies a pointer to a status to return (valid only if the
6544  PFN lock had to be released, ie: NULL was returned).
6545 
6546 Return Value:
6547 
6548  A non-null pointer to an inpage block if one is already available.
6549  The PFN lock is not released in this path.
6550 
6551  NULL is returned if no inpage blocks were available. In this path, the
6552  PFN lock is released and an entry is added - but NULL is still returned
6553  so the caller is aware that the state has changed due to the lock release
6554  and reacquisition.
6555 
6556 Environment:
6557 
6558  Kernel mode, PFN lock may optionally be held.
6559 
6560 --*/
6561 
6562 {
6563  PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT Support;
6564  PSLIST_ENTRY SingleListEntry;
6565 
6566 #if DBG
6567  if (OldIrql != MM_NOIRQL) {
6568  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
6569  }
6570  else {
6571  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() < DISPATCH_LEVEL);
6572  }
6573 #endif
6574 
6575  if (ExQueryDepthSList (&MmInPageSupportSListHead) != 0) {
6576 
6577  SingleListEntry = InterlockedPopEntrySList (&MmInPageSupportSListHead);
6578 
6579  if (SingleListEntry != NULL) {
6580  Support = CONTAINING_RECORD (SingleListEntry,
6581  MMINPAGE_SUPPORT,
6582  ListEntry);
6583 
6584 returnok:
6585  ASSERT (Support->WaitCount == 1);
6586  ASSERT (Support->u1.e1.PrefetchMdlHighBits == 0);
6587  ASSERT (Support->u1.LongFlags == 0);
6588  ASSERT (KeReadStateEvent (&Support->Event) == 0);
6589  ASSERT64 (Support->UsedPageTableEntries == 0);
6590 
6591  Support->Thread = PsGetCurrentThread();
6592 #if DBG
6593  Support->ListEntry.Next = NULL;
6594 #endif
6595 
6596  return Support;
6597  }
6598  }
6599 
6600  if (OldIrql != MM_NOIRQL) {
6601  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6602  }
6603 
6604  Support = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
6605  sizeof(MMINPAGE_SUPPORT),
6606  'nImM');
6607 
6608  if (Support != NULL) {
6609 
6610  KeInitializeEvent (&Support->Event, NotificationEvent, FALSE);
6611 
6612  Support->WaitCount = 1;
6613  Support->u1.LongFlags = 0;
6614  ASSERT (Support->u1.PrefetchMdl == NULL);
6615  ASSERT (KeReadStateEvent (&Support->Event) == 0);
6616 
6617 #if defined (_WIN64)
6618  Support->UsedPageTableEntries = 0;
6619 #endif
6620 #if DBG
6621  Support->Thread = NULL;
6622 #endif
6623 
6624  if (OldIrql == MM_NOIRQL) {
6625  goto returnok;
6626  }
6627 
6628  InterlockedPushEntrySList (&MmInPageSupportSListHead,
6629  (PSLIST_ENTRY)&Support->ListEntry);
6630 
6631  //
6632  // Pool had to be allocated for this inpage block hence the PFN
6633  // lock had to be released. No need to delay, but the fault must
6634  // be retried due to the PFN lock release. Return a status such
6635  // that this will occur quickly.
6636  //
6637 
6638  *Status = STATUS_REFAULT;
6639  }
6640  else {
6641 
6642  //
6643  // No pool is available - don't let a high priority thread consume
6644  // the machine in a continuous refault stream. A delay allows
6645  // other system threads to run which will try to free up more pool.
6646  // Return a status that will introduce a delay above us in an effort
6647  // to make pool available. The advantage of our caller executing the
6648  // delay is because he'll do this after releasing the relevant
6649  // working set mutex (if any) so the current process can be trimmed
6650  // for pages also.
6651  //
6652 
6653  *Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
6654  }
6655 
6656  if (OldIrql != MM_NOIRQL) {
6657  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6658  }
6659 
6660  return NULL;
6661 
6662 }

6664 VOID
6665 MiFreeInPageSupportBlock (
6666  IN PMMINPAGE_SUPPORT Support
6667  )
6668 
6669 /*++
6670 
6671 Routine Description:
6672 
6673  This routine returns the inpage support block to a list of freed blocks.
6674 
6675 Arguments:
6676 
6677  Support - Supplies the inpage support block to put on the free list.
6678 
6679 Return Value:
6680 
6681  None.
6682 
6683 Environment:
6684 
6685  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL or below.
6686 
6687 --*/
6688 
6689 {
6690  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() < DISPATCH_LEVEL);
6691 
6692  ASSERT (Support->Thread != NULL);
6693  ASSERT (Support->WaitCount != 0);
6694 
6695  ASSERT ((Support->ListEntry.Next == NULL) ||
6696  (Support->u1.e1.PrefetchMdlHighBits != 0));
6697 
6698  //
6699  // An interlock is needed for the WaitCount decrement as an inpage support
6700  // block can be simultaneously freed by any number of threads.
6701  //
6702  // Careful synchronization is applied to the WaitCount field so
6703  // that freeing of the inpage block can occur lock-free. Note
6704  // that the ReadInProgress bit on each PFN is set and cleared while
6705  // holding the PFN lock. Inpage blocks are always (and must be)
6706  // freed _AFTER_ the ReadInProgress bit is cleared.
6707  //
6708 
6709  if (InterlockedDecrement (&Support->WaitCount) == 0) {
6710 
6711  if (Support->u1.e1.PrefetchMdlHighBits != 0) {
6712  PMDL Mdl;
6713  Mdl = MI_EXTRACT_PREFETCH_MDL (Support);
6714  if (Mdl != &Support->Mdl) {
6715  ExFreePool (Mdl);
6716  }
6717  }
6718 
6719  if (ExQueryDepthSList (&MmInPageSupportSListHead) < MmInPageSupportMinimum) {
6720  Support->WaitCount = 1;
6721  Support->u1.LongFlags = 0;
6722  KeClearEvent (&Support->Event);
6723 #if defined (_WIN64)
6724  Support->UsedPageTableEntries = 0;
6725 #endif
6726 #if DBG
6727  Support->Thread = NULL;
6728 #endif
6729 
6730  InterlockedPushEntrySList (&MmInPageSupportSListHead,
6731  (PSLIST_ENTRY)&Support->ListEntry);
6732  return;
6733  }
6734  ExFreePool (Support);
6735  }
6736 
6737  return;
6738 }

6740 VOID
6741 MiHandleBankedSection (
6742  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
6743  IN PMMVAD Vad
6744  )
6745 
6746 /*++
6747 
6748 Routine Description:
6749 
6750  This routine invalidates a bank of video memory, calls out to the
6751  video driver and then enables the next bank of video memory.
6752 
6753 Arguments:
6754 
6755  VirtualAddress - Supplies the address of the faulting page.
6756 
6757  Vad - Supplies the VAD which maps the range.
6758 
6759 Return Value:
6760 
6761  None.
6762 
6763 Environment:
6764 
6765  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, working set mutex held.
6766 
6767 --*/
6768 
6769 {
6770  PMMBANKED_SECTION Bank;
6771  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6772  ULONG BankNumber;
6773  ULONG size;
6774 
6775  Bank = ((PMMVAD_LONG) Vad)->u4.Banked;
6776  size = Bank->BankSize;
6777 
6778  MiZeroMemoryPte (Bank->CurrentMappedPte, size >> PAGE_SHIFT);
6779 
6780  //
6781  // Flush the TB as we have invalidated all the PTEs in this range.
6782  //
6783 
6784  MI_FLUSH_PROCESS_TB (FALSE);
6785 
6786  //
6787  // Calculate new bank address and bank number.
6788  //
6789 
6790  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (
6791  (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)VirtualAddress & ~((LONG)size - 1)));
6792  Bank->CurrentMappedPte = PointerPte;
6793 
6794  BankNumber = (ULONG)(((PCHAR)PointerPte - (PCHAR)Bank->BasedPte) >> Bank->BankShift);
6795 
6796  (Bank->BankedRoutine) (BankNumber, BankNumber, Bank->Context);
6797 
6798  //
6799  // Set the new range valid.
6800  //
6801 
6802  RtlCopyMemory (PointerPte,
6803  &Bank->BankTemplate[0],
6804  size >> (PAGE_SHIFT - PTE_SHIFT));
6805 
6806  return;
6807 }
